\par }{\b\fs28\cf13 Elf PC Kits
\par }{\fs24 
\par Kits are optional additions to the campaign, allowing a player to add detail to his or her PC. These kits are collections of various abilities and disadvantages that can help a player better define his or her character.
\par    \tab Most of these kits are uniquely elven; although other races may have similar kits, the kits in this book are for elves only. The kits in the other }{\i\fs24 Complete Player's Handbook}{\fs24 
 series are also available for elves to take, unless explicitly stated otherwise.
\par    \tab Before using one of these kit
s, a player must first generate the character's initial statistics. First, roll ability scores and choose an elf subrace, an alignment, and a class. Then, choose the kit that's most appealing and assign proficiencies, money, equipment, and other details.

\par    \tab Once a player has chosen a particular kit for a PC, he or she cannot exchange it for a new one. Neither can a character have two kits. It is only possible to have one kit at a time.
\par    \tab If characters want to abandon a kit for any reason, they cannot select a new one, for the kit describes their development and growth. These PCs can abandon the kit's hindrances, but they also loses any benefits as well.
\par    \tab Characters can only use a kit that is specific to their class. That is, warriors may take one of th
e warrior kits, but cannot use the warrior/mage kits. Multiclass characters choose kits that are part of their class. For example, a mage/thief can use a mage kit, a thief kit, or a mage/thief kit. A warrior or a warrior/thief kit could not be selected, h
owever, because they contain elements that are totally foreign to that character.
\par    \tab In addition, although a player might want a multiclass character to specialize in a weapon, this is not possible. While some of the kits may echo weapon specialization, no one who is not a pure fighter can have a weapon specialization\emdash 
including rangers.
\par    \tab Each kit presented in this chapter is made up of twelve different parts. The first is a general description of the kit and the requirements of entry into that kit. Any who do not meet the requirements cannot take the kit for their character
\emdash }{\i\fs24 No Exceptions! }{\fs24 The remaining eleven parts are as follows:
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li720\nowidctlpar\tx-720\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls1\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnindent360 {\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls1\adjustright {\b\fs24 Role.}{\fs24 
 This is the role of the PC in general and in elven society in particular. Note that the exclusion of either male or female pronouns does not mean the kit is restricted to gender. All kits are available to both sexes.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li720\nowidctlpar\tx-720\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls1\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnindent360 {\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls1\adjustright {\b\fs24 Secondary Skills.}{\fs24 
 If a campaign does not use the proficiency rules, the character must take his secondary skills from this section rather than randomly rolling for them.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li720\nowidctlpar\tx-720\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls1\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnindent360 {\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls1\adjustright {\b\fs24 Weapon Proficiencies.}{\fs24 
 These are the weapon proficiencies required of the elf to fill the slots available. Usually, not all of these slots will be filled by the required weapons, leaving some degree of choice. Please note that weapon pro
ficiencies are not bonus proficiencies unless specified as such. Most are simply required, not actual bonuses.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li720\nowidctlpar\tx-720\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls1\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnindent360 {\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls1\adjustright {\b\fs24 Bonus Nonweapon Proficiencies.}{\fs24 
 Most kits provide some nonweapon proficiencies. These are free\emdash even if they belong to other character classes. Note: All }{\i\fs24 civilized }{\fs24 elves know Reading/Writing.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li720\nowidctlpar\tx-720\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls1\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnindent360 {\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls1\adjustright {\b\fs24 Recommended Nonweapon Proficiencies. }{\fs24 
